message.text:
BREAKING: Manila Mayor Honey Lacuna-Pangan suspends classes in both public and private schools in ALL LEVELS as well as work in local government offices in the City of Manila for Tuesday, September 3, 2024, due to #EntengPH.

Offices providing frontline services such as emergency response , peace and order, and basic and health services shall be exempted from the suspension.

Suspension of work for private companies shall be left to the discretion of their respective heads.

Memorandum circular No. 63 from the Office of the President suspends classes in public schools and government work in NCR and Region 4-A for September 3.

#WalangPasok

message.text:
NEWS ALERT: Manila City Mayor Francisco “Isko Moreno” Domagoso has ordered the suspension of classes in all levels for both public and private schools in the nation’s capital on August 8, 2019.

This after state weather bureau PAGASA declared a yellow rainfall warning over Metro Manila in an advisory issued at 11:30 am.

According to the advisory, flooding is possible in low-lying areas. Stay safe, Manilenos! 

#WalangPasok
